EXTRAS

In 1981, the public television anthology series &quot;The Golden Age of Television&quot; broadcast these eight shows. These broadcasts were preceded by substantial introductions hosted by well-known actors and including brief interviews with some cast and crew from the show. These introductions are included with each of the shows in the boxed set. Hosts include Eva Marie Saint, Keenan Wynn, Roddy McDowell, Merv Griffin, Cliff Robertson, Jack Klugman, Carl Reiner, and Julie Harris.





